8 Section 1. R.S. 40:2116(B)(8) and 2197.1 are hereby enacted to read as follows:
9 §2116. Facility need review
10 * * *
11 B. The following healthcare providers shall be subject to facility need review
12 to determine the need for a new or additional facility, provider, program, service, or
13 bed:
14 * * *
15 (8) Types one and two rural health clinics.
16 * * *
17 §2197.1. Equality in Medicaid reimbursement rates for rural health clinics
18 A. The secretary of the Louisiana Department of Health shall take all
19 necessary actions to equalize the Medicaid reimbursement rate between independent
20 rural health clinics, also known as type one rural health clinics, and provider-based
21 rural health clinics, also known as type two and three rural health clinics. In fiscal
22 years 2026-2027 and 2027-2028, the Louisiana Department of Health shall increase
23 the encounter rate that is in effect in the previous fiscal year for independent rural
24 health clinics by forty-one dollars and fifty cents. The annual Medicare Economic
25 Index inflationary adjustment shall be applied to this rate.
